  "plainText": "Hermit Drying Rack\nObject Info\nPerk\nDry Food items.\nMiscellaneous\n\"meatrack_hermit\"\nExclusive to:\n“Those look like they could use some meat.”\n–Wilson\n“Maybe I'll leave some meat here before I leave...”\n–Willow\n“Is sad and meat-less.”\n–Wolfgang\n“One can't survive long without food...”\n–Wendy\n“AS IF I WOULD HELP THAT OLD MEATSACK...”\n–WX-78\n“It seems our chitinous friend could use some assistance.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Whatcha think, Lucy? Do we have some meat to spare?”\n–Woodie\n“Perhaps if she were fed, she'd be less ill-tempered.”\n–Maxwell\n“I'd be cantankeröus töö if I were left withöut meat!”\n–Wigfrid\n“Maybe we could share some meat?”\n–Webber\n“It looks so bare... perhaps I could put some meat on it.”\n–Warly\n“Need food?”\n–Wormwood\n“Maybe I should give the old lady a hand.”\n–Winona\n“Her hooks are bare, but should I care?”\n–Wortox\n“These belong to crabby lady, florp.”\n–Wurt\n“Those are some pretty swell looking drying racks.”\n–Walter\n“Maybe I could help the poor old thing, if I have a spare minute or two...”\n–Wanda\nThe Hermit Drying Rack is a naturally spawning object exclusive to Don't Starve Together, introduced in Return of Them. Six of them can be found on the Hermit Island.\nThe Hermit Drying Rack works just like a Drying Rack, except that it cannot be destroyed or burned and can only dry one item at a time.\nContents\n1 Dryable Items\n2 Skins\n3 Assets\n4 Gallery\nDryable Items[edit | edit source]\nThe list of possible Food that can be dried:\nItem\nDried\nTime required\nSpoil Timer\n2 days\n20 days\n1 day\n20 days\n1 day\n15 days\n2 days\n20 days\n1 day\n20 days\n0.5 day\n15 days\n1 day\n15 days\n1 day\nx\n1 day\nx\n1 day\nx\n1 day\nx\n1 day\nx\n1 day\nx\n1 day\nx\n1 day\nx\n0.25 days\n20 days\nSkins[edit | edit source]\nMain article: Belongings\nThe Event skin does not drop normally. Instead, it is usable by everyone during the official Winter's Feast event.\nWoven - Elegant\nShelled Collection\nCoral Meat Rack\nAdd a deliciously fishy kick to your jerky!\nEvent\nThe Merrymaker Collection\nn/a\nn/a\nAssets[edit | edit source]\nHermit Drying RackThe MerrymakerCoral Meat Rack\nBuild\nIdle\nBurnt (Unused)\nBuild\nIdle\nBuild\nIdle\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nUI Slots concept art from Rhymes with Play stream.\nHermit Drying Rack Old UI.\nDSTDSRoGSWHam\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Together Structures\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/DLC/function/tags of these Things. Some of them are not even Structures.\nPlants\nNon-living objects\nCarcasses\nCraftable\nInanimate\nScrap\nAncient\nPillar\nCharacter Exclusive\nWeather Objects\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Structures\nPlants\nInanimate\nCraftable\nNaturally generating\nAncient\nPillars\nCharacter exclusive\nWeather Objects\nView or edit this template\nReign of Giants Structures\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/DLC/function/tags of these Things. Some of them are not even Structures.\nPlants\nNon-living objects\nCraftable\nInanimate\nAncient\nPillar\nCharacter Exclusive\nWeather Objects\nView or edit this template\nShipwrecked Structures\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/DLC/function/tags of these Things. Some of them are not even Structures.\nPlants\nNon-living objects\nCarcasses\nCraftable\nInanimate\nCharacter Exclusive\nWeather Objects\nView or edit this template\nHamlet Structures\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/DLC/function/tags of these Things. Some of them are not even Structures.\nPlants\nNon-living objects\nCraftable\nInanimate\nPig City\nAncient\nPillars\nCharacter Exclusive\nWeather Objects",
